HEADWORD: Pulvinated
<hw>Pul"vi*na`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pulvinatus</ets>, fr.
<ets>pulvinus</ets> a cushion, an elevation.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Curved convexly or swelled; <as>as, a
